1.5 Rental Receipt Generation
    (A complete question + step-by-step instructions + full code + sample output)

    This is a realistic and professional addition to the Rental System.
    When a user rents a vehicle, the system will automatically generate a receipt, showing:

    User name

    Vehicle details

    Rental date

    Price per day

    Total price (for this example: 1-day rental)

    Receipt number

    Timestamp

    Later, you can expand it to calculate number of days and total cost ‚Äî but we‚Äôll start simple.

    üìù QUESTION FOR STUDENTS (Assignment)
    üöó Add ‚ÄúRental Receipt Generation‚Äù Feature
    When a user rents a vehicle, the system should generate a text receipt automatically.

    The receipt must contain:
        Receipt number

        User name

        Vehicle details (model, type, price per day)

        Rental date

        Timestamp (real date/time system generated)

        A "Thank You" message

    The receipt must be saved into a file:
    receipt_<receiptNumber>.txt
    Example:
    receipt_101.txt
    receipt_102.txt
    ...
    Requirements:
        Receipt numbers should auto-increment

    The system should show:

    Receipt generated: receipt_101.txt
    The receipt must NOT overwrite previous receipts

    üí° HINTS FOR STUDENTS
    Use a static counter for receipt numbers, OR
    read the number from a file

    Use BufferedWriter or FileWriter

    Use LocalDateTime.now()

    Combine vehicle and user information

    Always save receipt inside a /receipts folder (optional)


    üß™ SAMPLE RECEIPT FILE OUTPUT (receipt_1.txt)
    ====== VEHICLE RENTAL RECEIPT ======
    Receipt No: 1
    Date Issued: 2025-02-11T14:23:45.723

    Customer: john

    Vehicle Information:
    Model: Toyota Corolla
    Type: Car
    Price per Day: $45.0

    Rental Date: 2025-02-11

    Thank you for renting with ABC Rentals!
    ====================================
    üß™ SAMPLE CONSOLE OUTPUT
